# Cursor Rules for algtools/actions

## Project Overview
This repository hosts reusable GitHub Actions and workflows used across the Algenium and Algtools ecosystem.

## Code Standards
- Follow GitHub Actions best practices
- Use semantic versioning for action releases
- Validate all workflows with actionlint
- Include comprehensive documentation for each action
- Use minimal permissions for GITHUB_TOKEN

## Structure
- `.github/actions/`: Custom reusable actions
- `.github/workflows/`: Reusable workflows and CI/CD
- `.github/tests/`: Test files and fixtures

## CI/CD
- All workflows must pass actionlint validation
- Use proper security practices (minimal permissions, pinned versions)
- Document all inputs, outputs, and secrets required

## Documentation
- Every action must have a README.md in its directory
- Include usage examples
- Document all inputs and outputs
- Specify required permissions
